<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="765" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857/131: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hinkle</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-21T17:00:00-05:00">March 21,
                                    1940—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>31. Your 51, March 15, 9 a.m. Please express to the Dominican Foreign
                            Secretary the gratification of the Department at the meeting of minds
                            which has taken place with regard to the <hi rend="italic">Hannover</hi>
                            incident and inform him that the following telegram is today being sent
                            to the American Embassy at Panama:</p>
                        <p>(Here copy telegram No. 33, March 21, 5 p.m. sent to Embassy,
                            Panama.)</p>
                        <p>Please ask the Foreign Secretary to telegraph his comments on these
                            drafts and on the proposed procedure to Dr. Garay, the Minister of
                            Foreign Affairs of Panama.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>